01:04:49,260 --> 01:04:52,020
I was asked, I was at a launch of a book

1316
01:04:52,020 --> 01:04:55,420
by Professor Paul Davis, a physicist,

1317
01:04:55,420 --> 01:04:58,260
and his book is called, Are We Alone?

1318
01:04:59,220 --> 01:05:01,900
And I was interviewed, and I was being interviewed

1319
01:05:01,900 --> 01:05:06,460
by a certain station called Premier Christian Radio.

1320
01:05:06,460 --> 01:05:07,300
I don't know whether you remember.

1321
01:05:07,420 --> 01:05:08,940
I remember the interview well.

1322
01:05:08,940 --> 01:05:11,580
It was one of the first times I'd had you on the show,

1323
01:05:11,580 --> 01:05:13,260
and I brought you on with Paul Davis.

1324
01:05:13,260 --> 01:05:14,340
That's right.

1325
01:05:14,340 --> 01:05:16,620
And Paul Davis said, as a scientist,

1326
01:05:16,620 --> 01:05:20,220
he thought that we weren't alone, we were alone,

1327
01:05:20,220 --> 01:05:22,940
but as a person, he hoped we weren't alone.

1328
01:05:22,940 --> 01:05:26,900
And then I was asked, did I believe

1329
01:05:26,900 --> 01:05:29,500
that there were other intelligence in the universe?

1330
01:05:29,500 --> 01:05:32,580
And I said, yes, and one very big one called God.

1331
01:05:33,580 --> 01:05:37,340
And quite seriously, from a Christian perspective,

1332
01:05:37,340 --> 01:05:40,660
there are other intelligences in the universe.

1333
01:05:40,660 --> 01:05:41,860
Of course there are.

1334
01:05:41,860 --> 01:05:45,700
And God is the greatest one, but there are others,

1335
01:05:45,700 --> 01:05:48,500
because we are told that there are beings,

1336
01:05:48,500 --> 01:05:53,500
in some sense, above us, the Bible calls them spirit beings.

1337
01:05:54,300 --> 01:05:58,420
They're not made of matters, we understand it,

1338
01:05:58,420 --> 01:06:00,300
angels and so on.

1339
01:06:00,340 --> 01:06:01,740
So there are others.

1340
01:06:01,740 --> 01:06:06,740
This whole universe is much more complex than we think.

1341
01:06:06,980 --> 01:06:11,980
And our vision, we don't see everything.

1342
01:06:12,500 --> 01:06:16,380
So I think there are, and it does matter infinitely,

1343
01:06:16,380 --> 01:06:20,260
because if we were the only intelligences around,

1344
01:06:20,260 --> 01:06:24,060
we'd be left with the question as to where we come from.

1345
01:06:24,060 --> 01:06:26,540
But because we know about God,

1346
01:06:26,540 --> 01:06:29,940
then we've got a huge answer to that question.

1347
01:06:30,660 --> 01:06:32,140
Thank you so much.

1348
01:06:32,140 --> 01:06:35,060
From the sublime to the almost ridiculous,

1349
01:06:35,060 --> 01:06:38,500
in this question, there are lots of theories

1350
01:06:38,500 --> 01:06:41,900
in our internet age floating around.

1351
01:06:41,900 --> 01:06:43,340
And interestingly, one of the ones

1352
01:06:43,340 --> 01:06:45,860
that has sort of had a bizarre revival,

1353
01:06:45,860 --> 01:06:48,260
is the idea that we're living on a flat earth.

1354
01:06:48,260 --> 01:06:51,700
And this has been, this is the most popular question,

1355
01:06:51,700 --> 01:06:53,020
according to the likes.

1356
01:06:53,020 --> 01:06:56,180
What do you think about the flat earth debate, John?

1357
01:06:56,180 --> 01:06:57,460
Nothing at all, really.

1358
01:06:57,580 --> 01:07:00,580
I mean, but in all seriousness, there's, for me,

1359
01:07:00,580 --> 01:07:03,580
it's a sign of the fact we live in an age

1360
01:07:03,580 --> 01:07:06,380
where almost anything can get airtight on these days.

1361
01:07:06,380 --> 01:07:07,220
And that's true.

1362
01:07:07,220 --> 01:07:11,420
It wasn't a cheek, I should say, that if people reject God,

1363
01:07:11,420 --> 01:07:13,380
they don't believe in nothing.

1364
01:07:13,380 --> 01:07:15,300
They end up believing in anything.

1365
01:07:15,300 --> 01:07:19,180
And it just shows there's masses of ridiculous things

1366
01:07:19,180 --> 01:07:20,180
that people believe.

1367
01:07:20,180 --> 01:07:22,260
And they don't believe in anything.

1368
01:07:22,260 --> 01:07:26,140
And it just shows there's masses of ridiculous things

1369
01:07:26,140 --> 01:07:27,380
that people believe.

1370
01:07:27,380 --> 01:07:29,700
And that is the thing that staggers me,

1371
01:07:29,700 --> 01:07:31,420
taking the question seriously.

1372
01:07:31,420 --> 01:07:33,100
They will believe that kind of thing,

1373
01:07:33,100 --> 01:07:36,260
where for which the evidence is all contrary.

1374
01:07:36,260 --> 01:07:41,260
And yet, when it comes to seriously set forward

1375
01:07:42,060 --> 01:07:44,420
arguments and reasons for believing in God,

1376
01:07:44,420 --> 01:07:46,000
they won't even listen to them.

1377
01:07:46,000 --> 01:07:50,540
There's a double think, and I would go as far as to say

1378
01:07:50,540 --> 01:07:52,500
that there's a reason for it.

1379
01:07:53,420 --> 01:07:56,980
There's a very interesting statement that Paul made,

1380
01:07:56,980 --> 01:08:00,220
that the God of this world has blinded the minds

1381
01:08:00,220 --> 01:08:02,500
of those who don't believe.

1382
01:08:02,500 --> 01:08:07,500
That there is an enemy who sets the thought forms

1383
01:08:07,700 --> 01:08:08,700
of the world.

1384
01:08:09,740 --> 01:08:14,140
And Paul analyzes the intellectual darkness

1385
01:08:14,140 --> 01:08:16,780
that comes about in Romans.

1386
01:08:16,780 --> 01:08:20,980
When people reject God, they end up worshiping stones

1387
01:08:20,980 --> 01:08:22,700
and inanimate things.

1388
01:08:22,700 --> 01:08:26,260
They ascribe creatorial power to nature

1389
01:08:26,260 --> 01:08:28,340
because they don't believe in God.

1390
01:08:28,340 --> 01:08:31,780
And some of it is utterly absurd.

1391
01:08:31,780 --> 01:08:33,300
And yet, that is what happens.

1392
01:08:33,300 --> 01:08:36,300
And I would describe it as intellectual darkness,

1393
01:08:36,300 --> 01:08:38,020
but there's an enemy behind it.

1394
01:08:39,500 --> 01:08:40,820
Thank you.

1395
01:08:40,820 --> 01:08:42,300
This is a very popular question.

1396
01:08:42,300 --> 01:08:44,820
What do you think, why do you think Christianity

1397
01:08:44,820 --> 01:08:49,020
is on the decline in Europe, especially amongst young people?

1398
01:08:51,300 --> 01:08:53,860
That's very complex, I think, historically.

1399
01:08:53,860 --> 01:08:57,340
You're probably better positioned to answer that than I am.

1400
01:08:58,820 --> 01:09:01,740
There are roots in history going back to the enlightenment

1401
01:09:01,740 --> 01:09:06,740
of the evils perpetuated by some professing branches

1402
01:09:06,980 --> 01:09:09,940
of the Christian church have died hard.

1403
01:09:09,940 --> 01:09:14,180
The fact that in the whole EU constitution,

1404
01:09:14,180 --> 01:09:17,020
the word God has not mentioned at all,

1405
01:09:17,020 --> 01:09:19,860
the fact that our major institutions

1406
01:09:19,860 --> 01:09:23,640
are all of them virtually as Tom Holland

1407
01:09:23,640 --> 01:09:26,340
and Jordan Peters and other people are pointing out

1408
01:09:26,340 --> 01:09:28,340
are all traceable back to scripture,

1409
01:09:28,340 --> 01:09:30,860
yet that's airbrushed out of history

1410
01:09:30,860 --> 01:09:34,580
so that we are educating young people.

1411
01:09:34,580 --> 01:09:37,020
We're, in that sense, brainwashing them

1412
01:09:37,020 --> 01:09:39,100
and not telling them the facts

1413
01:09:39,100 --> 01:09:42,140
so that they just don't know.

1414
01:09:42,140 --> 01:09:46,500
And it's not surprising.

1415
01:09:46,500 --> 01:09:48,900
You see, let me put it very crudely.

1416
01:09:48,940 --> 01:09:51,780
If you tell people constantly, young people,

1417
01:09:51,780 --> 01:09:54,140
that there's no meaning in life,

1418
01:09:54,140 --> 01:09:58,380
they are simply animals, moderately sophisticated animals,

1419
01:09:58,380 --> 01:10:00,860
they'll end up believing you.

1420
01:10:00,860 --> 01:10:03,900
And therefore, their behavior will not be governed

1421
01:10:03,900 --> 01:10:06,140
by any sense of morality.

1422
01:10:06,140 --> 01:10:09,240
And it is frightening to read things like this.

1423
01:10:09,240 --> 01:10:13,500
A class of students ask this,

1424
01:10:13,500 --> 01:10:15,660
give an example of a moral dilemma.

1425
01:10:15,660 --> 01:10:18,580
Answer, what is a moral dilemma?

1426
01:10:20,380 --> 01:10:23,220
We are in serious trouble, folks,

1427
01:10:23,220 --> 01:10:25,460
but I'm glad you said in Europe

1428
01:10:25,460 --> 01:10:27,080
because there are other parts of the world

1429
01:10:27,080 --> 01:10:30,180
where Christianity is growing and thriving

1430
01:10:30,180 --> 01:10:32,860
and they are often the parts

1431
01:10:32,860 --> 01:10:35,460
where there's been much more persecution.

1432
01:10:35,460 --> 01:10:37,980
And then somebody pointed out to me the other day,

1433
01:10:37,980 --> 01:10:39,980
if you take the whole of the Bible,

1434
01:10:39,980 --> 01:10:42,420
how much of it was written at a time

1435
01:10:42,420 --> 01:10:45,820
and there was no persecution and trouble, very little.

1436
01:10:45,820 --> 01:10:48,940
And we have had an experience in Europe,

1437
01:10:48,940 --> 01:10:51,220
at least until relatively recently,

1438
01:10:51,220 --> 01:10:55,260
without war for an unusual period of time.

1439
01:10:55,260 --> 01:10:58,060
And unfortunately, into the vacuum,

1440
01:10:59,020 --> 01:11:02,940
there has poured all this kind of stuff,

1441
01:11:02,940 --> 01:11:05,660
post-modernism, atheism, all the rest of it.

1442
01:11:05,660 --> 01:11:08,180
And it has had an effect in our society.

1443
01:11:09,180 --> 01:11:12,380
But please feel free to add to that, Justin,

1444
01:11:12,380 --> 01:11:14,100
because from your perspective...

1445
01:11:14,100 --> 01:11:15,700
I wouldn't disagree with anything

1446
01:11:15,700 --> 01:11:17,220
that you've said there, John.

1447
01:11:17,220 --> 01:11:20,500
I think that we are living in the wake,

1448
01:11:20,500 --> 01:11:22,540
if you like, of many different forces

1449
01:11:22,540 --> 01:11:25,500
that have led to the way in which religion

1450
01:11:25,500 --> 01:11:29,100
is now seen as a private hobby, almost.

1451
01:11:29,100 --> 01:11:32,380
And to that extent, it's part of the fact

1452
01:11:32,380 --> 01:11:35,300
that our cultures are increasingly mobile, fluid.

1453
01:11:35,300 --> 01:11:37,500
Many community institutions have broken down

1454
01:11:37,500 --> 01:11:40,900
because of the focus on individualism in our culture.

1455
01:11:40,900 --> 01:11:42,220
And so I think there's a lot of things.

1456
01:11:42,220 --> 01:11:44,740
And alongside that goes, obviously,

1457
01:11:44,740 --> 01:11:47,620
that this materialism, this story of materialism

1458
01:11:47,620 --> 01:11:50,780
that obviously convinces people without good foundation,

1459
01:11:50,780 --> 01:11:52,700
that there is no God and so on.

1460
01:11:52,700 --> 01:11:54,260
I think I'm encouraged,

1461
01:11:54,260 --> 01:11:56,460
and part of the story I tell in my new book

1462
01:11:56,460 --> 01:11:58,900
is that actually people can only live on

1463
01:11:58,900 --> 01:12:02,500
those thin versions of reality for so long, though,

1464
01:12:02,500 --> 01:12:04,820
until actually people do start to come back and ask,

1465
01:12:04,820 --> 01:12:07,180
is this the way life is meant to be lived?

1466
01:12:08,100 --> 01:12:09,380
And I'm encouraged, actually,

1467
01:12:09,380 --> 01:12:14,100
that I see a lot of young people almost,

1468
01:12:14,100 --> 01:12:16,660
as we reach a point where

1469
01:12:16,660 --> 01:12:19,780
there's almost no familiarity with the Christian story.

1470
01:12:19,780 --> 01:12:21,500
One of the good things about that

1471
01:12:21,500 --> 01:12:23,860
is that you don't have the assumption

1472
01:12:23,860 --> 01:12:25,340
that you know what it is.

1473
01:12:25,340 --> 01:12:27,660
And sometimes it's actually easier

1474
01:12:27,660 --> 01:12:29,260
to start telling people what it is

1475
01:12:29,260 --> 01:12:30,420
when they don't know anything about it,

1476
01:12:30,420 --> 01:12:32,380
rather than those who think they know what it is,

1477
01:12:32,380 --> 01:12:35,380
but actually have a rather false idea of it in their head.

1478
01:12:35,380 --> 01:12:38,060
So I think we should be encouraged.

1479
01:12:38,060 --> 01:12:40,700
I mean, let me skip to this question

1480
01:12:40,700 --> 01:12:42,900
since we're talking about this.

1481
01:12:42,900 --> 01:12:45,500
And this is obviously a lot of people here

1482
01:12:45,500 --> 01:12:47,860
from the Romanian diaspora.

1483
01:12:47,860 --> 01:12:49,420
And someone asked, what is your advice

1484
01:12:49,420 --> 01:12:51,900
for the Romanian community specifically,

1485
01:12:51,900 --> 01:12:53,580
the Christian Romanian community,

1486
01:12:53,580 --> 01:12:56,780
for improving the belief climate in the UK?

1487
01:12:56,780 --> 01:12:58,340
Any thoughts on that, John?

1488
01:13:00,020 --> 01:13:04,020
Well, I have had the privilege of being in Romania

1489
01:13:04,060 --> 01:13:05,540
several times.

1490
01:13:05,540 --> 01:13:08,580
The first time I went, I was poisoned deliberately

1491
01:13:08,580 --> 01:13:09,980
by the secret police.

1492
01:13:11,300 --> 01:13:12,140
Wow.

1493
01:13:12,140 --> 01:13:13,500
It nearly killed me.

1494
01:13:13,500 --> 01:13:14,460
Gosh.

1495
01:13:14,460 --> 01:13:17,580
And I look back to that and the Lord preserved me

1496
01:13:17,580 --> 01:13:20,620
because I went to visit some marvelous Christians there,

1497
01:13:20,620 --> 01:13:21,820
but I've been back since

1498
01:13:21,820 --> 01:13:23,980
and they don't feed you poison anymore.

1499
01:13:25,260 --> 01:13:27,900
And they don't have the poison.

1500
01:13:28,900 --> 01:13:31,180
I think I could say,

1501
01:13:31,220 --> 01:13:34,580
but you need to ask Samuel about that.

1502
01:13:34,580 --> 01:13:37,620
They haven't been infected by all the poisons

1503
01:13:37,620 --> 01:13:40,660
of atheism that we have in the West.

1504
01:13:40,660 --> 01:13:43,220
So I think you've got,

1505
01:13:43,220 --> 01:13:45,740
and what I saw in my brief visits,

1506
01:13:45,740 --> 01:13:49,780
you've got much more sense of togetherness as Christians.

1507
01:13:49,780 --> 01:13:51,020
Well, let's ask a Romanian.

1508
01:13:51,020 --> 01:13:53,460
Yes, I think Samuel needs to speak to this.

1509
01:13:53,460 --> 01:13:55,260
You'd probably be very well positioned

1510
01:13:55,260 --> 01:13:59,620
to this question of how the Romanian Christian community

1511
01:13:59,620 --> 01:14:03,660
can specifically encourage belief in the West.

1512
01:14:03,660 --> 01:14:06,140
Well, I think the Romanian diaspora community

1513
01:14:06,140 --> 01:14:09,500
is very strong here in London and in the UK.

1514
01:14:09,500 --> 01:14:12,380
There are many evangelical churches in London.

1515
01:14:12,380 --> 01:14:13,780
And I think one of the reasons

1516
01:14:13,780 --> 01:14:18,580
that Romanians believe in God and keep their faith,

1517
01:14:18,580 --> 01:14:22,260
although they live in a very secularized society

1518
01:14:22,260 --> 01:14:24,900
and culture is because of communism.

1519
01:14:24,900 --> 01:14:29,900
And communism promoted atheism as the national ideology.

1520
01:14:30,220 --> 01:14:34,180
And Romanians have lived this for several decades

1521
01:14:34,180 --> 01:14:36,300
and experienced what that means.

1522
01:14:36,300 --> 01:14:38,300
And it simply doesn't work.

1523
01:14:38,300 --> 01:14:41,300
So that's one of the reasons that Romanians

1524
01:14:41,300 --> 01:14:43,260
and Eastern Europe in general

1525
01:14:43,260 --> 01:14:45,700
remained a very religious society.

1526
01:14:45,700 --> 01:14:47,060
It still is.

1527
01:14:47,060 --> 01:14:49,140
And I think Romanians

1528
01:14:49,140 --> 01:14:51,420
and other international diaspora communities,

1529
01:14:51,420 --> 01:14:55,020
such as the Polish diaspora community, for example,

1530
01:14:55,020 --> 01:15:00,020
can and may indeed revive Christianity

1531
01:15:00,820 --> 01:15:05,540
and bring a new energy in terms of living faith

1532
01:15:05,540 --> 01:15:08,380
in a secular culture as the UK.

1533
01:15:08,380 --> 01:15:10,860
I think that's absolutely true.

1534
01:15:10,860 --> 01:15:14,460
And I spent many years,

1535
01:15:14,460 --> 01:15:18,820
I started going to Eastern Europe in 1976

1536
01:15:18,820 --> 01:15:22,980
and traveled many times, particularly to Hungary, Poland

1537
01:15:22,980 --> 01:15:25,300
and above all, East Germany.

1538
01:15:25,300 --> 01:15:29,100
And I came to the conclusion that many of our modern day

1539
01:15:29,100 --> 01:15:32,220
so-called new atheists or passainer

1540
01:15:32,220 --> 01:15:37,220
have not got a clue about what atheism does to a culture.

1541
01:15:38,020 --> 01:15:41,860
And as Romanians, you know,

1542
01:15:41,860 --> 01:15:44,220
and because you know,

1543
01:15:44,220 --> 01:15:48,700
you can be a force for enormous good in our society.

1544
01:15:48,700 --> 01:15:51,260
When people start talking about these things,

1545
01:15:51,260 --> 01:15:52,860
you could just say, just wait a minute,

1546
01:15:52,860 --> 01:15:54,460
let me tell you what it was like

1547
01:15:54,460 --> 01:15:57,660
to live under the Sicuritate and the secret police.

1548
01:15:57,660 --> 01:16:01,060
And I saw this again and again in East Germany,

1549
01:16:01,060 --> 01:16:03,420
which was almost Stalinist

1550
01:16:03,420 --> 01:16:05,340
and I went there many times.

1551
01:16:06,620 --> 01:16:09,060
You've got a huge contribution to make.

1552
01:16:09,060 --> 01:16:11,260
And I think Samuel's absolutely right.

1553
01:16:11,260 --> 01:16:15,780
And I would encourage you to be a source

1554
01:16:15,780 --> 01:16:19,860
of pushback against this kind of thing.

1555
01:16:19,860 --> 01:16:24,860
I remember once talking in Russia actually in Siberia

1556
01:16:25,180 --> 01:16:27,820
to an academician about the difference

1557
01:16:27,820 --> 01:16:30,060
between the East and the West.

1558
01:16:30,060 --> 01:16:34,140
And he said, in the both parts of the world,

1559
01:16:34,140 --> 01:16:38,380
you've got materialism, you've got the material, we haven't.

1560
01:16:39,380 --> 01:16:41,740
But it's the same philosophy.

1561
01:16:41,740 --> 01:16:44,140
And that's the tragedy,

1562
01:16:44,140 --> 01:16:47,380
the stuff that you were taught under Marxism

1563
01:16:47,380 --> 01:16:52,380
is very little distance below the surface

1564
01:16:52,860 --> 01:16:56,580
of some of the leading intellectuals in the West today.

1565
01:16:56,580 --> 01:17:00,140
It's the same materialism as a philosophy,

1566
01:17:00,140 --> 01:17:02,060
but it's mixed with the consumerism

1567
01:17:02,060 --> 01:17:03,940
that you didn't have in those days.

1568
01:17:03,940 --> 01:17:06,180
And because you know what it's like

1569
01:17:06,180 --> 01:17:10,820
to be deprived of many things because of an ideology,

1570
01:17:10,820 --> 01:17:13,500
the Christian ideology or worldview

1571
01:17:13,500 --> 01:17:15,340
is much more precious to you

1572
01:17:15,340 --> 01:17:16,740
because of what it's done

1573
01:17:16,740 --> 01:17:19,860
until you've a huge contribution to make.

1574
01:17:19,860 --> 01:17:21,940
Just before we go to a question from the floor,

1575
01:17:21,940 --> 01:17:23,620
there's just one more that links really well

1576
01:17:23,620 --> 01:17:25,860
in with what you've just been talking about, John,

1577
01:17:25,860 --> 01:17:27,340
which is Andrew, who asks,

1578
01:17:27,340 --> 01:17:29,300
can you share with us a short story

1579
01:17:29,300 --> 01:17:31,420
from your experience before 1990

1580
01:17:31,420 --> 01:17:35,140
behind the Iron Curtain that could help our faith?

1581
01:17:35,140 --> 01:17:37,460
Because this is a fascinating aspect of your life

1582
01:17:37,460 --> 01:17:40,260
that perhaps not that many people know that you moved

1583
01:17:40,460 --> 01:17:44,460
and worked among people in Soviet Russia and so on.

1584
01:17:44,460 --> 01:17:48,300
Yes, well, before 1990, I wasn't in Russia.

1585
01:17:48,300 --> 01:17:53,060
I went there first in 1989, 1990.

1586
01:17:53,060 --> 01:17:56,780
But let me go years before that to East Germany.

1587
01:17:56,780 --> 01:18:00,700
And I'll tell you one story of a girl called Esther.

1588
01:18:00,700 --> 01:18:03,020
And she was a very bright girl.

1589
01:18:03,020 --> 01:18:05,980
She'd been top of her class in school.

1590
01:18:05,980 --> 01:18:08,340
And I happened to be there.

1591
01:18:08,340 --> 01:18:09,500
I'm a German speaker.

1592
01:18:09,500 --> 01:18:12,660
That's why I could move easily in East Germany.

1593
01:18:12,660 --> 01:18:17,020
And she came home from school weeping her heart out

1594
01:18:17,020 --> 01:18:18,660
while we were there.

1595
01:18:18,660 --> 01:18:21,660
And we said, Esther, what's wrong?

1596
01:18:21,660 --> 01:18:23,980
She said, the teacher has just told me,

1597
01:18:23,980 --> 01:18:25,860
I've got to leave school and go and work

1598
01:18:25,860 --> 01:18:27,820
in a slipper factory.

1599
01:18:27,820 --> 01:18:32,820
Now, this girl had been top of her class in every year.

1600
01:18:33,540 --> 01:18:37,780
But at the age of 13, she was asked to take

1601
01:18:37,780 --> 01:18:42,780
an oath of public allegiance to the atheistic state.

1602
01:18:44,940 --> 01:18:48,140
And she said, I'm a Christian, I can't do that.

1603
01:18:48,140 --> 01:18:49,300
And she was crying.

1604
01:18:49,300 --> 01:18:51,100
And we were weeping with her.

1605
01:18:51,100 --> 01:18:54,180
But I said, Esther, what did you say to the teacher?

1606
01:18:54,180 --> 01:18:56,220
I'll never forget her answer.

1607
01:18:56,220 --> 01:18:59,780
She said, Uncle John, I said to the teacher,

1608
01:18:59,780 --> 01:19:04,540
sir, one day you will stand before God

1609
01:19:04,540 --> 01:19:08,700
and you will answer for what you've done to me this day.

1610
01:19:08,700 --> 01:19:10,140
I never forgot that.

1611
01:19:10,140 --> 01:19:14,480
It's steeled me to redouble my efforts

1612
01:19:14,480 --> 01:19:19,480
to fight this ideology for the rest of my life.

1613
01:19:19,740 --> 01:19:22,260
And that's what I've tried to do with God's help

1614
01:19:22,260 --> 01:19:27,260
to fight what is driving the most extreme things

1615
01:19:27,820 --> 01:19:28,660
on the planet.

1616
01:19:28,660 --> 01:19:31,420
And one of them is the persecution of the Uighurs.

1617
01:19:31,420 --> 01:19:36,420
But all this kind of stuff comes from not a rejection

1618
01:19:36,580 --> 01:19:39,420
of God, but a hatred of God.

1619
01:19:39,420 --> 01:19:43,340
And just that one thing encapsulates it.

1620
01:19:43,340 --> 01:19:44,460
Wonderful.

1621
01:19:44,460 --> 01:19:46,460
Let's have a question here.

1622
01:19:46,460 --> 01:19:49,500
Many wars are fought in the name of God.

1623
01:19:49,500 --> 01:19:52,820
If God really cares, why is he allowing these things

1624
01:19:52,820 --> 01:19:53,980
to happen?

1625
01:19:53,980 --> 01:19:56,860
In the next is even many lives are lost

1626
01:19:56,860 --> 01:19:59,660
in natural disasters, innocent lives.

1627
01:19:59,700 --> 01:20:02,500
Where is God when all these things happen?

1628
01:20:02,500 --> 01:20:03,340
Well, thank you.

1629
01:20:03,340 --> 01:20:06,300
That's the hardest question you can ask.

1630
01:20:06,300 --> 01:20:11,300
It's the hardest question for anyone of any worldview,

1631
01:20:11,860 --> 01:20:15,180
the problem of evil and suffering.

1632
01:20:15,180 --> 01:20:19,660
And I would want really to be fair to your question

1633
01:20:19,660 --> 01:20:22,780
to have an hour to talk about it at least

1634
01:20:22,780 --> 01:20:25,500
because there are no simplistic answers to this.

1635
01:20:25,500 --> 01:20:28,720
But I'll try and say something briefly.

1636
01:20:28,720 --> 01:20:33,160
You referred very briefly and concisely to two problems.

1637
01:20:33,160 --> 01:20:35,880
There's a problem of moral evil,

1638
01:20:35,880 --> 01:20:39,080
the bad things people do to one another, wars,

1639
01:20:39,080 --> 01:20:41,800
as we see it horribly these days.

1640
01:20:41,800 --> 01:20:45,120
Then there's a problem of what's called natural evil,

1641
01:20:45,120 --> 01:20:48,120
which is a bit of a misnomer.

1642
01:20:48,120 --> 01:20:50,280
And that is catastrophes, diseases,

1643
01:20:50,280 --> 01:20:54,760
cancers, tsunamis, earthquakes, all that kind of thing.

1644
01:20:54,760 --> 01:20:59,480
Now, how do we face that?

1645
01:20:59,480 --> 01:21:02,520
And I'm gonna cut to the middle of that

1646
01:21:02,520 --> 01:21:06,680
and tell you where I begin to see a possibility.

1647
01:21:06,680 --> 01:21:09,960
I've no simplistic answer because there isn't one.

1648
01:21:09,960 --> 01:21:12,940
But there are two ways of looking at it.

1649
01:21:14,400 --> 01:21:19,400
The person who's suffering sees it in a very different way

1650
01:21:20,440 --> 01:21:23,800
from say me who's watching the suffering.

1651
01:21:23,800 --> 01:21:26,320
In other words, cancer looks very different

1652
01:21:26,320 --> 01:21:29,120
in the eyes of a young mother who's just been told

1653
01:21:29,120 --> 01:21:31,200
she's got six months to live

1654
01:21:31,200 --> 01:21:34,400
and in the eyes of the oncologist who's treating her.

1655
01:21:34,400 --> 01:21:37,080
So there are two different sides

1656
01:21:37,080 --> 01:21:39,320
and the person that's watching tends

1657
01:21:39,320 --> 01:21:41,240
to have a more intellectual response.

1658
01:21:41,240 --> 01:21:42,920
They're full of big questions.

1659
01:21:42,920 --> 01:21:45,600
The other person is in utter pain

1660
01:21:45,600 --> 01:21:49,480
and needs comfort and help and encouragement.

1661
01:21:49,480 --> 01:21:52,160
Now, how do we face it?

1662
01:21:52,160 --> 01:21:55,240
Well, I'll tell you how I begin to face it.

1663
01:21:57,160 --> 01:22:00,840
The way you formulated the question is a very common one

1664
01:22:00,840 --> 01:22:02,960
and it's been there for centuries.

1665
01:22:02,960 --> 01:22:06,160
If there's a good and all powerful God,

1666
01:22:06,160 --> 01:22:10,480
how is it that the world is like this?

1667
01:22:10,480 --> 01:22:14,240
Now, let me look at it from the theoretical perspective first

1668
01:22:14,240 --> 01:22:17,480
because I'm afraid I'm a theorist, above all.

1669
01:22:17,480 --> 01:22:20,560
And if you want me to tell you about suffering,

1670
01:22:20,560 --> 01:22:22,640
just see me in the dentists.

1671
01:22:26,120 --> 01:22:31,120
Seriously though, many people respond to this

1672
01:22:31,160 --> 01:22:33,600
and say, therefore there's no God.

1673
01:22:34,720 --> 01:22:36,120
And many of my friends do

1674
01:22:36,120 --> 01:22:38,080
and I've been in Auschwitz many times

1675
01:22:38,080 --> 01:22:39,560
and I've wept every time.

1676
01:22:39,560 --> 01:22:42,000
It breaks my heart to see what's going on

1677
01:22:42,000 --> 01:22:44,360
in a country that I love in Ukraine.

1678
01:22:44,360 --> 01:22:46,040
Been there many times.

1679
01:22:46,040 --> 01:22:48,040
All those cities, I know them all.

1680
01:22:48,080 --> 01:22:52,280
So, how do we respond?

1681
01:22:52,280 --> 01:22:53,760
Well, there's no God.

1682
01:22:53,760 --> 01:22:55,080
Now, people that take that view

1683
01:22:55,080 --> 01:22:57,160
think they've solved the problem.

1684
01:22:57,160 --> 01:23:00,040
They've got rid of God, that's true.

1685
01:23:00,040 --> 01:23:03,400
But they've also got rid by definition of all hope.

1686
01:23:04,440 --> 01:23:06,960
The situation for them is totally hopeless

1687
01:23:06,960 --> 01:23:09,920
but actually they've got rid of the problem of evil.

1688
01:23:09,920 --> 01:23:12,280
Now, this is a more serious philosophical point.

1689
01:23:12,280 --> 01:23:14,320
So if you don't like philosophy, go to sleep

1690
01:23:14,320 --> 01:23:15,720
until you want to wake up.

1691
01:23:16,720 --> 01:23:19,640
The whole concept of evil,

1692
01:23:20,760 --> 01:23:25,280
I believe is directly related to the existence of God.

1693
01:23:25,280 --> 01:23:28,280
Dostoevsky, the famous Russian novelist,

1694
01:23:28,280 --> 01:23:29,440
said once, yes,

1695
01:23:29,440 --> 01:23:34,440
he's not exist, everything is permitted.

1696
01:23:34,440 --> 01:23:37,240
In other words, he didn't mean atheists can't behave.

1697
01:23:37,240 --> 01:23:42,240
He meant there's no reason for believing in good and evil.

1698
01:23:42,480 --> 01:23:45,120
And Richard Dawkins says exactly that.

1699
01:23:45,120 --> 01:23:48,640
He says, this universe is just what you'd expected to be.

1700
01:23:48,640 --> 01:23:52,160
If at bottom, there's no evil, no justice.

1701
01:23:52,160 --> 01:23:54,960
DNA just isn't, we dance to its music.

1702
01:23:54,960 --> 01:23:58,960
That's atheism, removing moral concepts.

1703
01:23:58,960 --> 01:24:01,280
But that doesn't work because Dawkins

1704
01:24:01,280 --> 01:24:05,440
doesn't even work for him because he knows he's a moral being

1705
01:24:05,440 --> 01:24:08,120
and therefore he talks about the problem of evil.

1706
01:24:08,120 --> 01:24:10,320
So there are many reasons that atheism

1707
01:24:10,320 --> 01:24:12,160
doesn't work intellectually,

1708
01:24:12,160 --> 01:24:14,960
but that's not going to help a person who's suffering.

1709
01:24:15,960 --> 01:24:18,640
Come now to the other side very briefly.

1710
01:24:19,720 --> 01:24:22,480
When I was a student, we used to have long discussions.

1711
01:24:22,480 --> 01:24:25,680
Well, if God is all powerful and he's all good,

1712
01:24:25,680 --> 01:24:29,480
and we never solved the problem, never.

1713
01:24:29,480 --> 01:24:32,640
I've never heard a good answer to the solution.

1714
01:24:32,640 --> 01:24:34,480
Now, I'm a mathematician

1715
01:24:34,480 --> 01:24:37,160
and when mathematicians try for centuries

1716
01:24:37,160 --> 01:24:40,360
to solve a problem, they usually ask themselves,

1717
01:24:40,360 --> 01:24:43,840
are we asking the right question?

1718
01:24:43,840 --> 01:24:46,560
So let me reformulate the question.

1719
01:24:47,720 --> 01:24:49,440
What are we faced with?

1720
01:24:49,440 --> 01:24:51,480
A mixed picture.

1721
01:24:51,480 --> 01:24:54,920
I call it beauty and barbed wire.

1722
01:24:54,920 --> 01:24:56,600
Beauty and bombs.

1723
01:24:56,600 --> 01:24:58,280
We look out at the starry night,

1724
01:24:58,280 --> 01:25:02,720
we see the Andromeda galaxy and it's absolutely magnificent

1725
01:25:02,720 --> 01:25:04,680
and then we turn on the television

1726
01:25:04,680 --> 01:25:06,840
and we watch what's happening in Ukraine.

1727
01:25:07,840 --> 01:25:11,040
Beauty and bombs.

1728
01:25:11,040 --> 01:25:12,960
We all have to face that.

1729
01:25:14,200 --> 01:25:19,200
Now, how are we going to face that mixed picture?

1730
01:25:20,400 --> 01:25:24,960
There's beauty, that's a mystery, if everything's evil.

1731
01:25:26,200 --> 01:25:28,360
How is it that we get like that?

1732
01:25:29,800 --> 01:25:33,760
And now I ask myself a question that's just as hard

1733
01:25:33,760 --> 01:25:35,600
and it's this.

1734
01:25:35,760 --> 01:25:38,440
We've all got to grant that it's a mixed picture.

1735
01:25:40,400 --> 01:25:43,280
Is there any evidence anywhere

1736
01:25:44,440 --> 01:25:47,720
that there's a God that we could trust with it?

1737
01:25:47,720 --> 01:25:49,760
That's an equally hard question.

1738
01:25:49,760 --> 01:25:53,720
But I believe that question brings us further

1739
01:25:53,720 --> 01:25:58,240
and it takes us directly to the cross

1740
01:25:59,080 --> 01:26:03,840
because the claim is, and I often say to people,

1741
01:26:03,840 --> 01:26:07,440
please listen to what Christianity claims

1742
01:26:07,440 --> 01:26:08,840
before you reject it.

1743
01:26:09,840 --> 01:26:14,520
The claim is that the one on the cross is God himself,

1744
01:26:14,520 --> 01:26:15,840
God incarnate.

1745
01:26:15,840 --> 01:26:17,880
So what, if I may put it bluntly,

1746
01:26:17,880 --> 01:26:20,800
is God doing on a cross, suffering?

1747
01:26:20,800 --> 01:26:25,120
Well, it certainly means that he hasn't remained distant

1748
01:26:25,120 --> 01:26:30,120
from our human suffering but has become part of it.

1749
01:26:30,400 --> 01:26:34,120
That's the first thing, the heart of God revealed.

1750
01:26:34,120 --> 01:26:36,800
Now of course, if that's where it ended,

1751
01:26:36,800 --> 01:26:39,040
we'd never have heard of Jesus.

1752
01:26:39,040 --> 01:26:43,400
The next bit is where the resurrection comes

1753
01:26:43,400 --> 01:26:45,480
into central role.

1754
01:26:45,480 --> 01:26:46,560
I would have no hope.

1755
01:26:46,560 --> 01:26:50,280
I wouldn't be sitting here trying to answer your question.

1756
01:26:50,280 --> 01:26:54,120
If I didn't believe that God had raised Jesus from the dead

1757
01:26:55,640 --> 01:26:58,040
and that's where the hope comes in.

1758
01:26:58,040 --> 01:27:03,040
You see, atheism is a hopeless faith, literally, hopeless.

1759
01:27:03,680 --> 01:27:04,960
There's no hope.

1760
01:27:04,960 --> 01:27:07,200
Now where can we get hope?

1761
01:27:07,200 --> 01:27:09,800
What has the atheist got to say to the young mother

1762
01:27:09,800 --> 01:27:11,160
with cancer?

1763
01:27:11,160 --> 01:27:12,000
Nothing.

1764
01:27:13,120 --> 01:27:15,600
Have I got anything to say as a Christian?

1765
01:27:16,960 --> 01:27:19,200
I can't promise her that she'd be cured

1766
01:27:19,200 --> 01:27:21,760
although we know God has the power to do it.

1767
01:27:21,760 --> 01:27:24,960
But what I can bring to her is a message of hope

1768
01:27:24,960 --> 01:27:29,960
that she can have a personal relationship with Christ

1769
01:27:30,120 --> 01:27:34,240
that will transcend death and have something

1770
01:27:34,240 --> 01:27:36,760
therefore to leave her children with.

1771
01:27:38,080 --> 01:27:41,680
Now, I was in Christchurch, New Zealand,

1772
01:27:42,880 --> 01:27:47,880
the same week as the earthquake and I spoke about this.

1773
01:27:48,240 --> 01:27:52,400
And when I'd finished, a huge audience,

1774
01:27:52,400 --> 01:27:54,280
one of the biggest that they'd seen in the church

1775
01:27:54,280 --> 01:27:58,920
for many years, there was a note left for me from a lady

1776
01:27:58,920 --> 01:28:01,520
and it just said, I lost my husband last week.

1777
01:28:03,080 --> 01:28:07,640
And she said, what you said is the first glimmer of hope

1778
01:28:07,640 --> 01:28:10,760
I've got, glimmer of hope.

1779
01:28:11,840 --> 01:28:15,360
And I believe scripture analyzes this very carefully.

1780
01:28:15,360 --> 01:28:18,560
I haven't time to go into it in detail, sir,

1781
01:28:18,560 --> 01:28:23,560
but in John 11, there is the story

1782
01:28:24,040 --> 01:28:26,240
of what happens when people suffer.

1783
01:28:26,240 --> 01:28:27,960
Lazarus died.

1784
01:28:27,960 --> 01:28:31,720
The sisters expected Jesus to be there and cure him.

1785
01:28:31,720 --> 01:28:34,960
He wasn't there, Jesus let the man die

1786
01:28:34,960 --> 01:28:38,360
and it nearly brought them to doubt the love of God.

1787
01:28:38,360 --> 01:28:41,360
And when he eventually came and Lazarus was dead,

1788
01:28:42,320 --> 01:28:46,440
the sister said, if you'd been here, he wouldn't have died.

1789
01:28:46,440 --> 01:28:48,240
And then he suddenly told Martha,

1790
01:28:48,240 --> 01:28:51,320
I am the resurrection and the life.

1791
01:28:51,320 --> 01:28:56,080
Now that whole story, I believe, shows us how this problem

1792
01:28:56,080 --> 01:29:00,440
on the one side can lead people to doubt the love of God,

1793
01:29:00,440 --> 01:29:03,480
but how Christ answers it by being the resurrection

1794
01:29:03,480 --> 01:29:04,320
on the life.

1795
01:29:04,320 --> 01:29:07,880
My final point is, I've tried to put this together

1796
01:29:07,880 --> 01:29:10,600
briefly in a little book that circled the world.

1797
01:29:10,600 --> 01:29:14,960
It's called, Where is God in a Coronavirus World?

1798
01:29:15,000 --> 01:29:17,360
But that'll have to do for that.

1799
01:29:17,360 --> 01:29:19,320
Well, thank you so much.

1800
01:29:19,320 --> 01:29:21,520
With apologies to the many other people

1801
01:29:21,520 --> 01:29:24,960
who have wanted to ask a question in person,

1802
01:29:24,960 --> 01:29:26,560
because time is drawn to a close,

1803
01:29:26,560 --> 01:29:30,560
I'm just gonna finish with a final question from Slido, John.

1804
01:29:30,560 --> 01:29:33,000
And this is, well, I'm gonna give you two actually,

1805
01:29:33,000 --> 01:29:35,600
because I think they're substantially the same question,

1806
01:29:35,600 --> 01:29:38,000
both very popular.

1807
01:29:38,000 --> 01:29:41,360
Someone asks, when Muslim people do what we do,

1808
01:29:41,360 --> 01:29:44,200
which is believing what they're taught by their parents

1809
01:29:44,640 --> 01:29:46,240
carrying on their faith,

1810
01:29:46,240 --> 01:29:49,320
what makes them wrong and thus right?

1811
01:29:49,320 --> 01:29:51,600
And to sum up that question, someone else asks,

1812
01:29:51,600 --> 01:29:55,120
how do you prove that Christianity is the true religion

1813
01:29:55,120 --> 01:29:57,480
and other religions are false?

1814
01:29:58,360 --> 01:29:59,760
Thanks for that.

1815
01:29:59,760 --> 01:30:04,760
I'm glad to hear that question because it's important.

1816
01:30:04,800 --> 01:30:09,080
I never try to answer that question without saying this.

1817
01:30:10,960 --> 01:30:13,480
When we start to talk about the differences

1818
01:30:13,520 --> 01:30:17,400
between religions, there is huge danger

1819
01:30:17,400 --> 01:30:20,280
of looking down at other people.

1820
01:30:21,320 --> 01:30:26,320
Now, it is very important to go back to something

1821
01:30:27,240 --> 01:30:31,000
that Samuel said in our interview.

1822
01:30:31,000 --> 01:30:36,000
Every man, woman on the planet is a person of infinite worth

1823
01:30:38,560 --> 01:30:40,920
made in the image of God.

1824
01:30:41,920 --> 01:30:45,320
And often you'll find that in essence,

1825
01:30:45,320 --> 01:30:49,920
the differences between religions are not moral differences.

